---
// BoundaryCutaway.astro - Cutaway diagram of the three physics-layer governance limits
---

<div class="boundary-cutaway-container">
  <div class="cutaway-title">Geometric Governance: Three-Layer Cutaway</div>

  <div class="cutaway-layers">
    <!-- Layer 1: Edge -->
    <div class="cutaway-layer layer-edge">
      <div class="layer-meta">Layer 1: Cognitive Edge</div>
      <div class="layer-header">FunctionGemma local execution</div>
      <div class="layer-body">
        Local 270M model constraints client intent at the device boundary. Ephemeral tool-call compiling before cloud transmission prevents unauthorized instruction expansion.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cutaway-connector"></div>

    <!-- Layer 2: Coupling -->
    <div class="cutaway-layer layer-coupling">
      <div class="layer-meta">Layer 2: Coupling Sheaf</div>
      <div class="layer-header">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</div>
      <div class="layer-body">
        JSON-RPC 2.0 schemas translate intent between incommensurable system geometries. Formally isolates the client's semantic network from privileged enterprise databases.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cutaway-connector"></div>

    <!-- Layer 3: Torus -->
    <div class="cutaway-layer layer-torus">
      <div class="layer-meta">Layer 3: Hardware Physics</div>
      <div class="layer-header">Ironwood 3D Torus topology</div>
      <div class="layer-body">
        Authority propagates by routing adjacency rather than security rank. Hardware interconnect wraps coordinates to horizontal peer verification loops.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cutaway-connector connector-to-anchor"></div>

    <!-- Base Anchor -->
    <div class="cutaway-anchor">
      <div class="anchor-meta">Irreducible Anchor</div>
      <div class="anchor-header">Human-Signed MCP Configuration File</div>
      <div class="anchor-body font-mono">
        /etc/mcp/config.json
      </div>
      <div class="amber-light-indicator"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cutaway-caption">
    Cross-section of structural containment. Authority flows downward through edge and protocol layers, terminating at the human-authored config signature.
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .boundary-cutaway-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-8) auto;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    max-width: var(--max-w-narrow);
  }
  .cutaway-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: bold;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .cutaway-layers {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .cutaway-layer {
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-mid);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .cutaway-layer:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--color-sovereign);
  }
  .layer-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  .layer-header {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .layer-body {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }
  .cutaway-connector {
    width: 2px;
    height: var(--space-4);
    background: var(--border-mid);
  }
  .connector-to-anchor {
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--border-mid), var(--color-sovereign));
  }
  
  /* base anchor styles */
  .cutaway-anchor {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-sovereign);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.08);
  }
  .anchor-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--color-sovereign);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }
  .anchor-header {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-sovereign);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .anchor-body {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background: var(--surface-3);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
  }
  
  .amber-light-indicator {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    right: var(--space-4);
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--color-sovereign);
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--color-sovereign);
  }
  
  .cutaway-caption {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
    width: 100%;
  }
</style>
